{"title_page": "John Cole (academic)", "text_new": "{{other people|John Cole}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n\n'''John Cole''' (1758\u20131819) was an [[Anglican]] priest and academic administrator at the [[University of Oxford]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/howardco/international/cornwall/cornwall_story.htm#GENERATION%206 | title=Generation 6 | work=Cornwall: Story | accessdate=July 13, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130013312/http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/howardco/international/cornwall/cornwall_story.htm |archive-date=November 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\nCole was originally from [[Marazion]] in [[Cornwall]], southwest [[England]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?pg=PA568&id=1hEUAAAAQAAJ | title=Illustrations of the Literary History of the Eighteenth Century | publisher=[[London]]: Nichols, Son, and Bentley | year=1826 | page=568 | chapter=The Rev. John Cole, D. D. | accessdate=July 13, 2011}}</ref> He was educated at [[Exeter College, Oxford]], where he gained a [[Master of Arts]] (1788), [[Bachelor of Divinity]] (1795) and [[Doctor of Divinity]] (1800).\n\nIn 1808, he was elected [[Rector (college)|Rector]] of [[Exeter College, Oxford]].\nWhile Rector at Exeter College, Cole was also [[Vice-Chancellor]] of [[Oxford University]] from 1810 until 1814.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/vc/position/previousvice-chancellors/|title=Previous Vice-Chancellors | publisher=[[University of Oxford]], UK|accessdate=July 13, 2011}}</ref>\nAt the time of his death in 1819, Cole was [[Pro-Vice-Chancellor]] at Oxford University, [[Chaplain]] to his [[William IV of the United Kingdom|Royal Highness the Duke of Clarence]], [[Rector (ecclesiastical)#Anglican churches|Rector]] of [[Yaverland]] in the [[Isle of Wight]], and [[Vicar]] of [[Gulval]] in Cornwall.\n\nHis brother was [[Christopher Cole (Royal Navy officer)|Captain Sir Christopher Cole]] KCB (1770\u20131836), a [[Royal Navy]] officer.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?pg=PA110&id=h-UKAAAAYAAJ | title=The Annual Biography and Obituary, Volume XXI | publisher=London: Longman, Rees, Orme, Brown, Green, & Longman | year=1837 | page=110 | chapter=Sir Christopher Cole, K.C.B. | accessdate=July 13, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Cornwall}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Exeter College, Oxford|Rector of Exeter College, Oxford]]\n| years=1808\u20131819\n| before=[[Henry Richards (clergyman)|Henry Richards]]\n| after=[[John Collier Jones]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Vice-Chancellor of Oxford University]]\n| years=1810\u20131814\n| before=[[John Parsons (academic)|John Parsons]]\n| after=[[Thomas Lee (clergyman)|Thomas Lee]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cole, John}}\n[[Category:1758 births]]\n[[Category:1819 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Marazion]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Exeter College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Rectors of Exeter College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Vice-Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:Pro-Vice-Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:English chaplains]]\n[[Category:19th-century English Anglican priests]]\n[[Category:Royal Navy chaplains]]\n", "text_old": "{{other people|John Cole}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n\n'''John Cole''' (1758\u20131819) was an [[Anglican]] priest and academic administrator at the [[University of Oxford]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/howardco/international/cornwall/cornwall_story.htm#GENERATION%206 | title=Generation 6 | work=Cornwall: Story | accessdate=July 13, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130013312/http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/howardco/international/cornwall/cornwall_story.htm |archive-date=November 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\nCole was originally from [[Marazion]] in [[Cornwall]], southwest [[England]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?pg=PA568&id=1hEUAAAAQAAJ | title=Illustrations of the Literary History of the Eighteenth Century | publisher=[[London]]: Nichols, Son, and Bentley | year=1826 | page=568 | chapter=The Rev. John Cole, D. D. | accessdate=July 13, 2011}}</ref> He was educated at [[Exeter College, Oxford]], where he gained a [[Master of Arts]] (1788), [[Bachelor of Divinity]] (1795) and [[Doctor of Divinity]] (1800).\n\nIn 1808, he was elected [[Rector (college)|Rector]] of [[Exeter College, Oxford]].\nWhile Rector at Exeter College, Cole was also [[Vice-Chancellor]] of [[Oxford University]] from 1810 until 1814.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/vc/position/previousvice-chancellors/|title=Previous Vice-Chancellors | publisher=[[University of Oxford]], UK|accessdate=July 13, 2011}}</ref>\nAt the time of his death in 1819, Cole was [[Pro-Vice-Chancellor]] at Oxford University, [[Chaplain]] to his [[William IV of the United Kingdom|Royal Highness the Duke of Clarence]], [[Rector (ecclesiastical)#Anglican churches|Rector]] of [[Yaverland]] in the [[Isle of Wight]], and [[Vicar]] of [[Gulval]] in Cornwall.\n\nHis brother was [[Christopher Cole (Royal Navy officer)|Captain Sir Christopher Cole]] KCB (1770\u20131836), a [[Royal Navy]] officer.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?pg=PA110&id=h-UKAAAAYAAJ | title=The Annual Biography and Obituary, Volume XXI | publisher=London: Longman, Rees, Orme, Brown, Green, & Longman | year=1837 | page=110 | chapter=Sir Christopher Cole, K.C.B. | accessdate=July 13, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Exeter College, Oxford|Rector of Exeter College, Oxford]]\n| years=1808\u20131819\n| before=[[Henry Richards (clergyman)|Henry Richards]]\n| after=[[John Collier Jones]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Vice-Chancellor of Oxford University]]\n| years=1810\u20131814\n| before=[[John Parsons (academic)|John Parsons]]\n| after=[[Thomas Lee (clergyman)|Thomas Lee]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cole, John}}\n[[Category:1758 births]]\n[[Category:1819 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Marazion]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Exeter College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Rectors of Exeter College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Vice-Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:Pro-Vice-Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:English chaplains]]\n[[Category:19th-century English Anglican priests]]\n[[Category:Royal Navy chaplains]]\n", "name_user": "Gazamp", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:AddedPortal:Cornwall", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Cole_(academic)"}
