{"title_page": "List of Estonian flags", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe national '''flag of [[Estonia]]''' is a [[tricolour (flag)|tricolour]] featuring three equal horizontal bands of [[blue]] (top), [[black]], and [[white]]. The normal size is 105 \u00d7 165&nbsp;cm. In [[Estonian language|Estonian]] it is colloquially called the \"''sinimustvalge''\" (literally \"blue-black-white\"), after the colours of the bands. The flag became associated with [[Estonians|Estonian]] [[nationalism]] and was used as the [[national flag]] (''riigilipp'') when the [[Estonian Declaration of Independence]] was issued on February 24, 1918. The flag was formally adopted on November 21, 1918. On December 12, 1918 was the first time the flag was raised as the national symbol atop of the [[Pikk Hermann]] Tower in Tallinn.<ref>[http://www.estemb.org/estonia/history/aid-780 Estonia's Blue-Black-White Tricolour Flag at estemb.org]</ref>\n<br />\nThe following is a '''list of [[Flag of Estonia|flags of]] [[Estonia]]'''.\n\n== National flag and state flag ==\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|-  bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! width=\"110\"|Flag!!width=\"100\"|Date!!width=\"250\"|Use!!width=\"250\"|Description\n|-\n| [[File:Flag of Estonia.svg|100px|border]] || 1918\u20131940<br/>1944 <br />1988/1990\u2013present|| State flag and civil ensign || Dimensions are 7:11; colors were standardized in 2014.\n|}\n\n== Governmental flags ==\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|-  bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! width=\"110\"|Flag!!width=\"100\"|Date!!width=\"250\"|Use!!width=\"250\"|Description\n|-\n| [[File:Flag of the President of Estonia.svg|100px|border]] || 1992\u2013present <br/> 1927<ref>http://www.ra.ee/dgs/_purl.php?shc=ERA.31.2.1041a