\n[[Category:Disease-related deaths in Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{One source|date=April 2014}}\n{{Infobox royalty\n| name         = Princess Karoline Mathilde\n| full name    = {{lang-de|Viktoria Friederike Auguste Marie Karoline Mathilde}}\n| title        = Duchess of Schleswig-Holstein\n| reign        = 27 April 1931 \u2013 20 February 1932\n| consort      = yes\n| house        = [[House of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg|Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg]]\n| spouse       = [[Friedrich Ferdinand, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein]]\n| issue        = [[Princess Victoria Adelaide of Schleswig-Holstein|Victoria Adelaide, Duchess of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha]]<br>[[Princess Alexandra Victoria of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Alexandra Victoria, Princess August Wilhelm of Prussia\n]]<br>[[Princess Helena Adelaide of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Helena Adelaide, Princess Harald of Denmark]]<br>[[Princess Adelaide of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Adelaide Louise, Princess of Solms-Baruth]]<br>[[Wilhelm Friedrich, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein]]<br>[[Princess Karoline Mathilde of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Karoline Mathilde, Countess Hans of Solms-Baruth]]\n| image        = Princess Karoline Mathilde of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg.jpg\n| image_size         = 225px\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date|1860|1|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Augustenborg, Denmark|Augustenborg]], [[Jutland]], [[Denmark]]\n| death_date   = {{Death date and age|1932|2|20|1860|1|25|df=y}}\n| death_place  = Gr\u00fcnholz, [[Province of Schleswig-Holstein]], [[Free State of Prussia]], [[Weimar Republic]]\n| father       = [[Frederick VIII, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein]]\n| mother       = [[Princess Adelheid of Hohenlohe-Langenburg]]\n}}\n\n'''Princess Karoline Mathilde of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg''' (25 January 1860, in [[Augustenborg, Denmark|Augustenborg]], [[Jutland]], [[Denmark]] &ndash; 20 February 1932, in Gr\u00fcnholz, [[Province of Schleswig-Holstein]], [[Free State of Prussia]], [[Weimar Republic]]) was the second-eldest daughter of [[Frederick VIII, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein]] and his wife [[Princess Adelheid of Hohenlohe-Langenburg]].\n\n==Family==\nKaroline Mathilde's elder sister, [[Augusta Viktoria of Schleswig-Holstein|Augusta Viktoria]] was German Empress and Queen of Prussia as the wife of [[Wilhelm II, German Emperor]]. Karoline Mathilde was [[Duke of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Duchess of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] and later Duchess of Schleswig-Holstein as the wife of [[Friedrich Ferdinand, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Friedrich Ferdinand]]. Karoline's maternal grandmother [[Princess Feodora of Leiningen|Princess Feodora]] of [[Principality of Leiningen|Leiningen]] was the [[Sibling#Half-sibling|half-sister]] of [[Queen Victoria of the United Kingdom|Queen Victoria]].\n\n==Marriage and issue==\nKaroline Mathilde married [[Friedrich Ferdinand, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein|Friedrich Ferdinand]], the eldest son of [[Friedrich, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] and [[Princess Adelheid of Schaumburg-Lippe]] and a nephew of [[Christian IX of Denmark]], on 19 March 1885 at [[Przemk\u00f3w|Primkenau]]. Friedrich Ferdinand and Karoline Mathilde had six children:\n\n*[[Princess Victoria Adelaide of Schleswig-Holstein|Princess Victoria Adelaide of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] (31 December 1885 \u2013 3 October 1970)\n*[[Princess Alexandra Victoria of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] (21 April 1887 \u2013 15 April 1957)\n*[[Princess Helena Adelaide of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] (1 June 1888 \u2013 30 June 1962)\n*[[Princess Adelaide of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] (19 October 1889 \u2013 11 June 1964)\n*[[Wilhelm Friedrich, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein]] (23 August 1891 \u2013 10 February 1965)\n*[[Princess Karoline Mathilde of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] (11 May 1894 \u2013 28 January 1972)\n\nAfter the overthrow of the Hohenzollern dynasty at the end of [[World War I]], Karoline and her family lived quietly, seldom seen outside Gr\u00fcnholz Castle.<ref name=nyt1>{{Citation|title=Princess Karoline Dies at 72 in Germany|newspaper=The New York Times|date=21 February 1932}}</ref>\n\nKaroline died on 20 February 1932, aged 72,  at their castle. A few years previously, she had suffered an attack of heart disease and never completely recovered. Her husband was the only family member present on her deathbed.<ref name=nyt1/>\n\n==Titles and styles==\n*25 January 1860 \u2013 19 March 1885: ''Her Serene Highness'' Princess Karoline Mathilde of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg\n*19 March 1885 \u2013 27 November 1885: ''Her Highness'' The Hereditary Princess of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg\n*27 November 1885 \u2013 27 April 1931: ''Her Highness'' The Duchess of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg\n*27 April 1931 \u2013 20 February 1932: ''Her Highness'' The Duchess of Schleswig-Holstein\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|1= 1. '''Princess Karoline Mathilde of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg'''\n|2= 2. [[Frederick VIII, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein]]\n|3= 3. [[Princess Adelheid of Hohenlohe-Langenburg]]\n|4= 4. [[Christian August II, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg]]\n|5= 5. [[Countess Louise Sophie of Danneskiold-Sams\u00f8e|Countess Louise Sophie af Danneskiold-Sams\u00f8e]]\n|6= 6. [[Ernst I, Prince of Hohenlohe-Langenburg]]\n|7= 7. [[Princess Feodora of Leiningen]]\n|8= 8. [[Frederick Christian II, Duke of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg]]\n|9= 9. [[Princess Louise Auguste of Denmark]]\n|10= 10. [[Christian Conrad, Count of Danneskiold-Sams\u00f8e|Christian Conrad, Count af Danneskiold-Sams\u00f8e]]\n|11= 11. Johanne Henriette Valentine Kaas af Mur\n|12= 12. [[Karl Ludwig, Prince of Hohenlohe-Langenburg]]\n|13= 13. [[Countess Amalie Henriette of Solms-Baruth]]\n|14= 14. [[Emich Carl, Prince of Leiningen]]\n|15= 15. [[Princess Victoria of Saxe-Coburg-Saalfeld]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg]]|25 January|1860|20 February|1932|[[House of Oldenburg]]}}\n{{s-reg|de}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Duke of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Duchess consort of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg]] | years=27 November 1885\u201327 April 1931| before=[[Princess Adelheid of Schaumburg-Lippe|Adelheid of Schaumburg-Lippe]]| after=Herself as Duchess consort of Schleswig-Holstein}}\n{{s-pre}}\n|-\n{{s-vac|last=[[Princess Dorothea of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha|Dorothea of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha]]|reason=}}\n{{s-tul|title=[[Duke of Schleswig-Holstein|Duchess consort of Schleswig-Holstein]]|years=27 April 1931\u201320 February 1932|reason=[[Austro-Prussian War|Duchy annexed by Prussia in 1866]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Princess Marie Melita of Hohenlohe-Langenburg|Marie Melita of Hohenlohe-Langenburg]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Princesses of Schleswig-Holstein}}\n{{Princesses of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg}}\n{{Princesses of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg by marriage}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg, Princess Karoline Mathilde of}}\n[[Category:1860 births]]\n[[Category:1932 deaths]]\n[[Category:House of Augustenburg|Karoline Mathilde]]\n[[Category:Princesses of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Gl\u00fccksburg|Karoline Mathilde]]\n[[Category:People from Augustenborg, Denmark]]\n[[Category:Princesses of Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Augustenburg|Karoline Mathilde]]\n[[Category:Disease-related deaths in Germany]]\n", "name